JOHANNESBURG - World Cup holders Germany have retained the top spot in the FIFA men's team rankings after the latest round of international matches while Belgium has climbed to third ahead of the 2018 finals in Russia. A total of 133 matches were played in March, including international friendlies and 13 competitive games in the AFC Asian Cup. NEW #FIFARANKING
		
